      <Value><![CDATA[<p>The UHR awards recognise outstanding and innovative projects and teams that have led transformational change in their organisations.</p>
<p>UHR provides top quality development, networking and communications to support Human Resources professionals in Higher Education in the UK. </p>
<p>Dee Denholm, Head of Human Resources at QMU, said: “QMU’s HR team is delighted to have been shortlisted for a UHR award in the category of Exceptional HR.</p>
<p>“The team was the only Scottish university to be shortlisted alongside three other universities out of 143 universities in the UK, so this is a great achievement.”</p>
<p>UHR is the professional organisation for Human Resources practitioners in the United Kingdom and Republic of Ireland universities.</p>
<p>Learn more about <a href="https://www.uhr.ac.uk/" title="Universities Human Resources">Universities Human Resources on their website</a>.</p>]]></Value>
